On each face, roughly parallel to the sides, run two bands of elongated punch marks in a vertical direction Each band is about 15mm wide, but very irregular. The marks seem to have been made with a tool like a blunt chisel with a convex edge. The impressions are spindle shaped and about 13mm long x 1.5mm wide.

publications: To be published in Hull Mus. Br. Impl. Cat (1941?)?
remarks: Good early br. age type, but could be foreign as well as British. cf. see J.E. Fossamon, Ostskand Norden und d. Allzsten Metallzeit.
